Worth keeping in mind if you plan to use raspberry. On other hand VPN server would have small footprint on card write cycles

So far the limited lifespan of SD card is the only concern I have with using it as Web server. For example if you were to hammer your SD card with non-stop writes at full speed it would last only about 20-30 days. But by using card of much larger capacity than needed and tweeking Linux to cut down on some non essential writes (ie system logs)  you can get 10-20 years usage time. So I can only guess in server for low traffic website it should last as long.

##Please note that we now recommend campers use their Campsite’s Facebook group for chatting instead of their campsite’s Gitter chatroom. 
We are doing this because few of our Campsite Gitter chatroooms have active synchronous discussions, and about 1/3rd of conversations consist of someone saying “hello” and not getting a response. We’ve removed this Gitter room from our Campsite directory. Still, we will keep it open for archival purposes, and you can keep using it if you’d like.
